modules.description: This module implements the L-BFGS optimization algorithm for minimizing or maximizing a differentiable objective function over a structured set of parameters. It operates on parameter values of type `prms` defined by the input module `P`, and works specifically with functions that map these parameters to a scalar value of type `Owl.Algodiff.D.t`. It is used to perform limited-memory gradient-based optimization in machine learning and numerical computation tasks where the objective function and its gradient can be computed efficiently.

This module implements the L-BFGS optimization algorithm for minimizing or maximizing a differentiable objective function over structured parameters. It operates on parameter values of type `prms` and works with functions mapping these parameters to scalar values of type `Owl.Algodiff.D.t`. It is used for efficient limited-memory gradient-based optimization in machine learning and numerical computation tasks where the objective function and its gradient are efficiently computable.
